WEBVTT

00:02.169 --> 00:03.504
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> The Vampire Diaries:

00:03.671 --> 00:08.259
I don't know what we were or what we're
supposed to be, but I've never felt more alive.

00:09.927 --> 00:11.387
JO:
In our coven's tradition...

00:11.554 --> 00:14.432
...after their 22nd birthday,
the twins merge their strength.

00:14.598 --> 00:16.809
- The weaker one dies.
- I'll find a way.

00:16.976 --> 00:18.185
I'm not gonna let you die.

00:18.352 --> 00:22.398
I hate you for ruining our friendship, and
I think that I deserve better than that.

00:22.565 --> 00:25.276
STEFAN: I haven't been there for her.
Caroline needed me...

00:25.443 --> 00:27.653
...and I ran away.

00:27.820 --> 00:30.197
You're dying, Mom,
and we're out of options.

00:30.364 --> 00:32.908
Which is why I gave my blood
to a cancer patient...

00:33.075 --> 00:34.326
...and I healed him.

00:34.493 --> 00:37.038
I am not ready to lose you now.

00:37.204 --> 00:40.499
I want you to live for me.

00:40.666 --> 00:42.626
Everything's gonna be okay.

00:53.637 --> 00:55.264
[THUDDING]

01:10.029 --> 01:11.864
[GLASS SHATTERS]

01:18.537 --> 01:20.206
[CLANKING]

01:35.971 --> 01:38.349
[CREAKING]

02:05.042 --> 02:06.585
[GASPS]

02:09.630 --> 02:11.132
Caroline.

02:11.298 --> 02:12.716
Colin?

02:12.883 --> 02:15.094
- What the hell did you do to me?
- What?

02:19.056 --> 02:21.350
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

02:22.101 --> 02:24.895
- Hey.
- My mom's still sleeping, don't wake her up.

02:25.062 --> 02:27.106
- What happened?
- I don't know. He was fine...

02:27.273 --> 02:30.651
...when we left him at Duke, remember?
He was running around and pain-free...

02:30.818 --> 02:33.404
...and scarfing down disgusting
vending machine food.

02:33.571 --> 02:35.573
Yeah, well, clearly he's not fine now.

02:35.739 --> 02:38.659
I thought you compelled him to forget
everything after you fed him blood.

02:38.826 --> 02:40.828
- How did he find you?
- I don't know.

02:43.789 --> 02:45.791
What if this blood isn't even his?

02:48.335 --> 02:51.088
Is there any chance your mom
signed the house over to you?

02:51.255 --> 02:54.008
I don't know, maybe.
She's been running around like crazy...

02:54.175 --> 02:56.802
...saying she needs
to get her ducks in a row.

03:09.440 --> 03:11.317
He's a vampire.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.111
Which means
after you fed him your blood...

03:15.446 --> 03:17.114
He died.

03:29.752 --> 03:32.296
Calculator. Calculator.

03:32.463 --> 03:35.466
Where is the calculator?

03:35.633 --> 03:39.178
Of course. Under the
catatonic serial killer.

03:46.393 --> 03:48.229
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:48.395 --> 03:50.356
- Sandwich?
- I can't.

03:50.522 --> 03:52.900
I'm, uh, late for my volunteer shift
at the hospital.

03:53.067 --> 03:54.902
Okay. Ooh. That's new.

03:55.611 --> 03:58.405
Oh, yeah. Jo made me
a new daylight ring.

03:58.572 --> 04:00.574
- You like?
- Depends. Does it work?

04:00.741 --> 04:03.118
- I'm here, aren't I?
- Yeah, inside in the shade.

04:04.078 --> 04:06.956
I know everyone has their doubts
about Jo's magic.

04:07.122 --> 04:10.000
She has an entire month to get stronger
and win the merge with Kai.

04:10.834 --> 04:13.420
So a little bit of support
wouldn't kill anybody.

04:13.587 --> 04:15.798
Speaking of killing people...

04:17.882 --> 04:21.637
Still counting sheep, or whatever the hell
you psychopaths dream of.

04:21.803 --> 04:26.183
Alaric's gone out of town to get some
mystical thingamabob to give Jo an edge.

04:26.642 --> 04:30.229
And your job is to babysit Kai,
not smother him with a pillow.

04:30.813 --> 04:31.855
Fine.

04:32.022 --> 04:34.858
He starts twitching,
give him 50 milligrams of pentobarbital.

04:35.025 --> 04:37.111
You're so cute when you're all doctorly.

04:39.280 --> 04:41.282
Oh, hey, you forgot this.

04:44.952 --> 04:46.745
You're not free tonight, are you?

04:46.912 --> 04:48.622
I know this little Italian joint...

04:48.789 --> 04:52.042
...that has eggplant so good,
you actually think you're eating people.

04:53.627 --> 04:55.879
And I happen to have
a weird eggplant obsession.

04:56.046 --> 04:57.381
- Perfect.
- Great.

04:57.548 --> 05:02.386
Maybe after that, go to the art house
theater. They're playing some French flick.

05:02.761 --> 05:05.889
- I don't speak French, Damon.
- Not to see the movie, silly.

05:06.765 --> 05:09.643
To hide in the back
and throw popcorn at hipsters.

05:13.689 --> 05:16.775
Wait, we've gone on this date already,
haven't we?

05:17.276 --> 05:19.695
Damon, that's cheating, okay?

05:19.862 --> 05:22.406
- You already know everything about me.
- Cheating?

05:22.573 --> 05:25.909
- Cheating's erasing all our epic memories.
- I'm serious.

05:26.076 --> 05:30.622
Look, if we're gonna do this, then we
can't just pick up where we left off.

05:30.956 --> 05:33.125
Because I don't remember where that is.

05:33.292 --> 05:36.628
I understand.
Where would you like to start?

05:36.795 --> 05:40.758
At the beginning.
I'm off at 6, you can pick me up then.

05:41.091 --> 05:42.551
- Fine.
- Fine.

05:42.718 --> 05:43.886
- Great.
- Great.

05:44.053 --> 05:45.262
Good.

05:45.429 --> 05:47.723
- Bye.
- Bye.

05:47.890 --> 05:49.516
[DOOR CLOSES]

05:52.019 --> 05:55.189
How about Atlantis?

05:55.356 --> 05:58.108
Or, like, the Sea of Tranquility?

05:58.275 --> 06:00.152
- On the moon?
- Mm-hm.

06:00.319 --> 06:04.281
- I hear it's nice there, it's very tranquil.
- Mm-hm.

06:04.448 --> 06:07.242
I'm serious. Like, pick a real place.

06:07.409 --> 06:11.538
Why are we talking about spending spring
break anywhere other than this tiny bed?

06:12.373 --> 06:16.543
Which we should probably leave
at some point today.

06:16.710 --> 06:18.796
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

06:18.962 --> 06:21.548
- Ignore that.
MR. PARKER: Olivia, you home?

06:21.715 --> 06:24.593
- Olivia?
- Oh, my God, he's early.

06:24.760 --> 06:27.012
- Who's early?
- Sweetheart, it's your old man.

06:27.513 --> 06:30.349
- Here, put this on.
- Your dad? What's he doing here?

06:30.516 --> 06:34.520
He wants to take Luke and me
out to dinner. Hide.

06:36.397 --> 06:38.148
Dad, hi.

06:38.315 --> 06:40.317
I thought we were meeting later.

06:40.484 --> 06:43.821
Well, we were, but I wanted a couple
of extra minutes with my girl.

06:43.987 --> 06:45.489
Oh.

06:45.656 --> 06:46.824
Happy birthday.

06:50.035 --> 06:51.245
Thanks.

06:55.207 --> 06:58.168
I adjusted Mrs. Murphy's dosage
of fentanyl. Keep an eye on her. Thanks.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.514
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

07:18.772 --> 07:20.107
[SIGHS]

07:20.524 --> 07:21.984
Should I call it?

07:22.985 --> 07:25.195
Time of death, anybody's guess.

07:25.696 --> 07:27.906
Well, in the magical win column...

07:28.073 --> 07:31.702
...I walked across campus without
bursting into flames, so there's that.

07:31.869 --> 07:33.370
COLIN: Ungh!
- I need help.

07:38.542 --> 07:41.336
JO: I had Duke send over
Colin's medical records.

07:41.503 --> 07:44.381
This head scan is from earlier this week.

07:44.548 --> 07:46.258
This one...

07:46.800 --> 07:49.470
...was taken right here 10 minutes ago.

07:49.636 --> 07:53.265
- See all that red?
- I'm no doctor, but that guy is screwed.

07:53.432 --> 07:58.687
So the blood didn't heal him,
it sped up his cancer and killed him.

07:58.854 --> 08:02.900
So now I have a stage 10 cancer patient,
which by the way, doesn't exist...

08:03.066 --> 08:06.111
...who is beyond terminally ill
and a vampire.

08:06.278 --> 08:08.739
All of his emotions are heightened
and he can't die.

08:08.906 --> 08:10.991
DAMON: Can someone tell me
why I was called here...

08:11.158 --> 08:14.411
...to listen to the story
of Colin the cancer vamp?

08:14.578 --> 08:16.538
Caroline fed me her blood last night.

08:18.248 --> 08:20.542
So the same thing is gonna happen to me.

08:27.758 --> 08:29.760
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

08:33.764 --> 08:34.806
Hi.

08:35.515 --> 08:36.975
- Any news?
- No.

08:37.142 --> 08:39.352
Not yet, it's a little
outside Jo's expertise.

08:39.520 --> 08:40.604
[SIGHS]

08:40.770 --> 08:44.316
Did you know that Caroline was
gonna give her mom vampire blood?

08:44.483 --> 08:46.568
Yeah, I was there when it healed Colin.

08:46.735 --> 08:50.489
And then you left. And then he died.
So it didn't...

08:50.656 --> 08:53.075
...actually heal him. It did the opposite.

08:53.242 --> 08:57.829
- Caroline had every reason to think it'd work.
- Yeah, but you didn't, Stefan.

08:57.996 --> 09:00.123
You're, what, like 165 years old?

09:00.457 --> 09:02.626
You've worked as a paramedic at hospitals.

09:02.793 --> 09:06.296
So that makes me an expert
in supernatural cancer treatment?

09:06.463 --> 09:11.134
I just wish you'd done a little bit more
research. Or waited like a day.

09:11.301 --> 09:15.472
Because you were thinking so rationally
when Damon died. Right?

09:15.973 --> 09:19.643
Her mother is terminal.
You didn't see the hope in her eyes...

09:19.810 --> 09:22.396
...when she thought
maybe her mother didn't have to die.

09:22.563 --> 09:25.857
And I didn't wanna be the one
to take that away from her.

09:31.446 --> 09:32.823
Um...

09:32.990 --> 09:35.284
Jo has an idea.

09:37.911 --> 09:40.414
JO: Medically speaking,
this is our best option.

09:40.581 --> 09:44.126
If vampire blood is the issue,
then a full transfusion of human blood...

09:44.293 --> 09:46.837
...might stabilize her condition.

09:47.337 --> 09:50.215
Please sound less confident, doc.

09:50.382 --> 09:52.759
Look, we are in uncharted territory here.

09:52.926 --> 09:55.846
This isn't just a medical problem, Damon,
it's a magical one.

09:56.013 --> 09:58.557
Well, then you're uniquely qualified.

09:59.182 --> 10:00.684
Witch doctor and all.

10:01.018 --> 10:03.937
Now you believe in my magic. Gee, thanks.

10:04.605 --> 10:08.025
Unfortunately, this goes beyond
any witch ability I've ever heard of.

10:08.191 --> 10:10.193
But, please, if you have a better plan...

10:10.736 --> 10:12.571
...I'm all ears.

10:14.281 --> 10:16.491
Why did you tell me
your birthday was in two weeks?

10:16.658 --> 10:18.368
To avoid this exact conversation.

10:18.702 --> 10:21.204
Am I wearing too much eyeliner?

10:21.371 --> 10:23.707
If you and Luke are 22,
you're old enough to merge.

10:23.874 --> 10:26.752
That's why Luke and I will use
our Wonder Twin powers of persuasion.

10:26.918 --> 10:29.713
Make Dad think that Jo's powerful enough
to overpower Kai...

10:29.880 --> 10:32.132
...and Luke and I
won't have to do the merge.

10:33.592 --> 10:36.219
You're wearing way too much makeup.
He shouldn't be here.

10:36.386 --> 10:39.306
He's not staying.
And why are you wearing a tie?

10:39.473 --> 10:43.393
I'm about to ask the leader of the Gemini
to let us out of a centuries-old tradition.

10:43.560 --> 10:45.395
Kind of need him to take me seriously.

10:45.562 --> 10:48.732
- You should let me talk to him.
- Really bad idea.

10:50.400 --> 10:54.071
- Promise me that you'll stay of it.
- What happens if you don't convince him?

10:54.404 --> 10:56.698
- We will.
- You die.

10:56.865 --> 10:58.909
You and Luke merge, Luke wins...

10:59.076 --> 11:00.410
...you die.

11:00.577 --> 11:02.079
Do you trust me?

11:03.455 --> 11:04.665
Do I have a choice?

11:05.624 --> 11:07.459
Then don't worry.

11:08.460 --> 11:09.878
You're not gonna lose me.

11:27.604 --> 11:28.814
Hey.

11:28.980 --> 11:32.442
"Hey, the blood transfusions are stopping
the cancer from eating her alive"...

11:32.609 --> 11:35.654
...or "Hey, is there a sheriff-sized space
available in the crypt"?

11:35.821 --> 11:38.657
I don't know. Jo's still running some tests
to find that out.

11:38.824 --> 11:40.826
She should be out in a minute.

11:43.787 --> 11:46.998
I don't know if you remember this,
but Liz and I are pretty close.

11:47.457 --> 11:48.500
Yeah.

11:48.667 --> 11:51.461
I mean, as far as humans go, she's...

11:52.295 --> 11:53.463
...tolerable.

11:56.049 --> 11:58.552
I can see how much you care about her,
but we all do.

11:58.719 --> 12:02.556
So if there's anything we can do
to fix this, trust me, we will.

12:02.848 --> 12:04.474
Yeah.

12:17.237 --> 12:19.322
- H i.
- Hey.

12:19.489 --> 12:22.159
The coffee machine's broken.
What kind of hospital is this?

12:22.325 --> 12:26.329
If you can't fix a coffee machine, then how
are you supposed to be able to fix people?

12:26.496 --> 12:27.998
Sure you don't need real food?

12:28.498 --> 12:33.253
There's probably a machine around here
that vends O-positive.

12:33.712 --> 12:36.506
I screwed up, bigtime.

12:36.673 --> 12:39.384
- Why did I feed her that blood?
- You were trying to help.

12:39.551 --> 12:43.013
No, I was trying to fix something
that I had no business trying to fix.

12:43.180 --> 12:45.932
It's like textbook definition
of control freak from hell.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.059
Listen, you are an optimist.

12:48.518 --> 12:50.395
You wanna believe anything is possible...

12:50.562 --> 12:53.690
...and that is exactly what your mom
needs to hear right now.

12:55.358 --> 12:57.027
Okay?

12:57.944 --> 12:59.112
[COLIN YELLS]

13:00.280 --> 13:01.531
That's Colin's room.

13:01.698 --> 13:03.200
[YELLS]

13:05.869 --> 13:07.704
I can't die.

13:11.082 --> 13:12.209
Why can't I die?

13:12.375 --> 13:15.045
Hey, hey, calm down, calm down.
It's okay. It's okay.

13:15.212 --> 13:16.421
It's not okay.

13:16.880 --> 13:18.924
I'm in agony.
I can hear my tumors growing.

13:19.090 --> 13:21.885
We'll try to help,
but just please stop hurting yourself.

13:23.136 --> 13:25.722
You wanna help me? Help me die.

13:27.015 --> 13:29.017
[RIPPING NOISE]

13:31.520 --> 13:32.896
Why the hell did you do that?

13:33.063 --> 13:35.398
He made a wish, I granted it.

13:38.610 --> 13:40.320
The blood transfusion didn't work.

13:42.239 --> 13:44.115
So you didn't just kill him, blondie.

13:45.242 --> 13:46.618
That's enough, Damon.

13:46.785 --> 13:48.912
No. It's fine.

13:49.079 --> 13:51.915
He's just saying
what everyone else is thinking.

13:54.084 --> 13:56.253
I killed my mom.

13:59.422 --> 14:00.924
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:04.261 --> 14:05.512
[LINE RINGING]

14:05.679 --> 14:08.431
RECORDING:
<i>Hi, it's Caroline. Leave a message.</i>

14:08.598 --> 14:10.976
Caroline, where are you? Call me.

14:11.142 --> 14:13.687
Or better idea, just...

14:14.104 --> 14:16.106
Just come back.

14:21.152 --> 14:24.364
- Hey.
- Hey.

14:24.656 --> 14:26.449
How are you feeling?

14:26.616 --> 14:29.411
Like a human pin cushion.

14:31.621 --> 14:35.542
So, what's the verdict?

14:35.709 --> 14:37.210
Did the blood swap work?

14:39.170 --> 14:43.216
We're not sure yet.
I mean, Jo's still doing some tests.

14:45.635 --> 14:48.847
You shouldn't lie to sick people, Elena.
It's bad karma.

14:52.809 --> 14:56.146
They thought it would slow down
the cancer cells from replicating.

14:57.188 --> 14:59.316
But it didn't work.

15:00.859 --> 15:02.485
I'm sorry.

15:04.863 --> 15:06.031
How's Caroline?

15:06.197 --> 15:08.742
She's good.
She just ran out to get some food.

15:08.909 --> 15:10.368
Elena.

15:10.869 --> 15:12.078
She just took off.

15:13.914 --> 15:17.876
- And now I can't find her.
- She won't forgive herself for this, will she?

15:18.585 --> 15:20.045
Hey.

15:23.006 --> 15:25.717
I'll make sure that we find her.

15:26.092 --> 15:28.011
I promise.

15:31.389 --> 15:33.308
Thank you.

15:43.526 --> 15:44.861
Good. You're here.

15:45.028 --> 15:47.030
I actually need a second opinion.

15:47.197 --> 15:49.866
I kind of like this because sunflowers
are her favorite flower...

15:50.033 --> 15:54.454
...but at the same time, I was also thinking
they're a little too over-the-top cheerful...

15:54.621 --> 15:55.956
...for a memorial service.

15:56.706 --> 16:01.127
So this was the second option. Um...

16:01.294 --> 16:05.382
Because roses are classic, right?
I mean, especially in this shade of pink.

16:05.548 --> 16:09.052
Obviously, I would change out the vase,
but, ahem...

16:11.054 --> 16:15.266
If you're thinking of saying something to make
me feel better, don't. I don't deserve it.

16:15.433 --> 16:16.559
- I wasn't.
- Good.

16:16.726 --> 16:20.063
I was actually thinking that you have
far more important things to do...

16:20.230 --> 16:22.565
...than plan a memorial service
for your mother...

16:23.942 --> 16:26.361
...who is still alive, by the way.

16:26.528 --> 16:29.364
Yeah, but all of this
still needs to be done, right?

16:29.781 --> 16:34.619
She's not gonna wanna live out the rest of
her life as a vampire in excruciating pain.

16:34.786 --> 16:40.375
I should do something I'm good at instead
of making things worse. Which arrangement?

16:42.293 --> 16:45.255
Caroline, you took a risk.

16:45.422 --> 16:47.799
It didn't pay off, but
you did it out of love.

16:49.801 --> 16:52.137
You made your mother sicker. Okay?

16:54.347 --> 16:58.226
But what are you gonna do now? Are you
just gonna bury your head in the sand?

16:58.393 --> 16:59.853
I don't...

17:01.104 --> 17:04.941
- I don't know what to say to her.
- You don't have to say anything to her.

17:05.108 --> 17:07.109
Just sit with her.

17:07.277 --> 17:11.614
I can't. I can't even face her.

17:13.282 --> 17:15.492
Look, when I was young...

17:16.036 --> 17:19.204
...my mom, she got really sick.

17:20.330 --> 17:25.795
And instead of spending time with her,
I did everything I could to avoid her.

17:26.588 --> 17:29.924
Like picking out her favorite flowers...

17:30.091 --> 17:32.802
...or walking into town
to get the tea that she liked.

17:33.219 --> 17:36.181
And I pretended like I
was doing it for her.

17:36.347 --> 17:38.224
But I wasn't.

17:38.725 --> 17:42.562
I was just afraid to see her like that.

17:44.814 --> 17:47.400
And then my dad, he, uh...

17:48.068 --> 17:51.571
He sent her away, and she died.

17:54.240 --> 17:57.368
I would give anything
to have one more day with her.

18:02.082 --> 18:04.793
What if she can't forgive me?

18:04.959 --> 18:07.337
She doesn't think there's anything
to forgive.

18:09.255 --> 18:11.883
She just wants you to be with her.

18:15.053 --> 18:16.554
[SIGHS]

18:36.449 --> 18:38.368
You're refusing to merge?

18:38.535 --> 18:40.703
We wanna consider other options.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.372
There are no other options.

18:42.539 --> 18:46.793
If a set of twins doesn't merge, the Gemini
bloodline will cease to exist upon my death.

18:46.960 --> 18:50.713
That means the entire coven will die.
Is that what you want?

18:50.880 --> 18:54.551
No, of course not.
But you are in perfect health.

18:54.717 --> 18:58.555
Kai is on ice.
That means we have time to figure this out.

18:58.721 --> 19:01.349
There's nothing to figure out.
This is what you were born to do.

19:01.516 --> 19:03.893
No, Dad. This is why Kai and Jo were born.

19:04.060 --> 19:08.106
We're the backup plan you bred because you
thought your first batch had a design flaw.

19:08.273 --> 19:10.024
Kai is a psychopath.

19:10.191 --> 19:12.569
- An extremely dangerous one.
LIV: Dad...

19:12.735 --> 19:15.405
...Jo can do this. She can win.

19:15.572 --> 19:18.074
All we're asking
is that you give her a chance.

19:18.241 --> 19:20.535
I'm not asking you to do anything
I haven't done myself.

19:20.952 --> 19:22.328
That's easy for you to say.

19:22.787 --> 19:25.248
You merged with your twin brother
and you won.

19:25.415 --> 19:26.749
You didn't drop dead.

19:26.916 --> 19:28.918
It doesn't work like that, and you know it.

19:29.085 --> 19:31.921
One will absorb traits from the other.

19:32.088 --> 19:34.924
Both of your souls will unite
into a new being.

19:35.091 --> 19:37.468
Who looks exactly like me.

19:38.052 --> 19:41.055
Yeah. I know I'm stronger than Liv.

19:41.431 --> 19:43.308
So that means I will win if we merge.

19:43.474 --> 19:46.853
So you can put whatever poetic spin
you want on it...

19:47.020 --> 19:49.606
...but I will be killing my own sister.

19:49.772 --> 19:50.982
I can't do that to her.

19:58.364 --> 20:01.284
Bad timing, Lockwood, I'm in a mood.

20:01.951 --> 20:03.661
What the hell are you doing?

20:05.872 --> 20:08.291
I'll make it easier.
I'll give you multiple choice.

20:08.458 --> 20:09.918
A, I'm being an idiot.

20:10.084 --> 20:13.963
B, I have anger issues, I'm a puny human,
I have to pick on people while they sleep.

20:14.130 --> 20:17.383
C, A and B are both correct.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.802
[TYLER GRUNTS AND COUGHS]

20:19.969 --> 20:23.806
Liv's dad's in town. She's trying to
convince him to let Jo and Kai do the merge.

20:23.973 --> 20:28.645
Thought you'd come grab Kai as a failsafe in
case Papa Parker says no to Liv and Luke.

20:28.811 --> 20:31.397
You just turn him loose
and he merges with Jo anyway.

20:31.564 --> 20:33.358
Huh? While I appreciate your efforts...

20:33.524 --> 20:37.987
...he's a psycho-freak magic siphon. I'm
not gonna just let you walk out with him.

20:44.869 --> 20:49.666
I could kiss you right now,
you beautiful moron.

20:49.832 --> 20:51.167
What are you talking about?

20:51.709 --> 20:53.836
[TYLER GRUNTING]

20:54.003 --> 20:55.296
DAMON:
Yep.

20:55.713 --> 20:57.090
That stuff works really well.

20:58.132 --> 21:01.678
Nighty-night.
That should keep you down for an hour.

21:02.428 --> 21:04.347
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

21:07.767 --> 21:10.687
- Not a good time.
- Well, I'm sorry to hear that, twin-derella.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.563
Big pitch going south, is it?

21:13.398 --> 21:15.024
Where's Tyler?

21:15.191 --> 21:17.527
Your boyfriend and I have come up
with a solution.

21:17.694 --> 21:19.988
A Hail Mary but everybody
gets what they need.

21:20.154 --> 21:23.908
I just have to ask Papa Parker one
question, so you mind putting him on?

21:24.075 --> 21:25.535
I wanna talk to Tyler.

21:25.702 --> 21:28.705
He's, uh, out at the moment.

21:39.966 --> 21:41.801
- Yes?
<i>- Hello, sir.</i>

21:41.968 --> 21:43.678
Damon Salvatore here.

21:43.845 --> 21:45.263
We had Thanksgiving together.

21:45.972 --> 21:49.100
Anyway, I've been sitting here Googling
celestial events happening today.

21:49.267 --> 21:52.979
And I was just curious,
would a Mercury-Venus conjunction...

21:53.146 --> 21:56.691
...give you enough juice to do
a little Gemini merge party?

21:56.858 --> 21:58.109
Why?

21:58.276 --> 22:01.279
<i>I'm gonna take that answer as a yes.
So here's the situation.</i>

22:01.446 --> 22:05.825
I'm gonna need you to use that planet party
to merge your set of blond twins ASAP.

22:05.992 --> 22:09.329
Unfortunately, your formerly comatose son
is gonna be on the loose...

22:09.495 --> 22:11.581
...and hell-bent on
beating you to the punch.

22:16.919 --> 22:18.880
Rise and shine, you little weasel.

22:21.758 --> 22:25.595
Ooh. Trying to pop a blood vessel
in my brain? Sorry, not gonna work.

22:25.762 --> 22:30.683
Looks like that magic you sucked up drained
away while you were asleep, good for me.

22:32.518 --> 22:35.605
But don't worry,
I know where you can get more.

22:37.648 --> 22:40.151
- You really think I'm gonna trust you?
- No.

22:40.318 --> 22:41.611
And I'm not gonna trust you.

22:41.778 --> 22:44.447
I happen to need a magic siphon,
and you're the only game in town.

22:48.242 --> 22:49.369
H i.

22:51.704 --> 22:53.039
[SIGHS]

22:55.792 --> 22:58.127
Let's discuss my fee.

23:04.008 --> 23:06.594
All right, I need a 12-gauge needle, stat.

23:07.804 --> 23:10.139
Don't know what I'm gonna do with it,
but I need it.

23:10.306 --> 23:12.141
You're not a doctor, stop playing games.

23:12.475 --> 23:15.561
I'm a vampire, and I will rip your head off
if you screw this up.

23:15.728 --> 23:18.773
What she said, so do your stupid
little magic-suction trick...

23:18.940 --> 23:21.859
...and suck the magic out of her.
Right now.

23:22.026 --> 23:24.362
I get what you two see in each other.

23:24.529 --> 23:26.989
It's very dys-fun-ctional.

23:27.990 --> 23:31.160
Heh. See what I did?
Stressing the "fun" in "dysfunctional."

23:31.327 --> 23:34.622
Just get on with it, Kai.
Listening to you talk makes me wanna die.

23:36.082 --> 23:37.291
That's good.

23:41.671 --> 23:43.339
[EXHALES]

23:44.173 --> 23:46.342
[MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY]

23:46.509 --> 23:48.010
Is it working?

23:48.177 --> 23:49.262
I have no idea.

23:53.015 --> 23:55.059
What the hell is going on?

23:55.768 --> 23:56.978
What is he doing here?

23:57.145 --> 24:00.690
Hey, sis. Little busy.
Be with you in a jiffy.

24:00.857 --> 24:03.151
- Elena?
- I'm gonna let Damon explain.

24:03.317 --> 24:04.360
Yeah.

24:06.028 --> 24:07.822
I'm staying with you.

24:10.408 --> 24:13.327
- Have you actually lost your mind?
- Hey, shh, listen.

24:13.870 --> 24:16.831
Liz was gonna die in eight hours
if the magic kept doing its thing.

24:16.998 --> 24:20.751
He steals magic. You made it through med
school. Figured you knew where I was going.

24:20.918 --> 24:25.506
If you think Kai's doing this out of the
goodness of his heart, he doesn't have one.

24:27.008 --> 24:28.092
What's the price?

24:29.177 --> 24:30.803
He wants to merge.

24:31.387 --> 24:32.555
Tonight.

24:43.816 --> 24:46.235
There. All done.

24:47.445 --> 24:48.779
Sheriff, hey.

24:48.946 --> 24:50.948
How are you feeling? You okay?

24:51.115 --> 24:53.409
Yeah. Yeah, I think so.

24:55.203 --> 24:57.330
[GROANING]

24:57.497 --> 24:58.956
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

24:59.123 --> 25:00.416
Oh, my God. No, no, no.

25:00.583 --> 25:04.086
- I think she's having a heart attack.
KAI: That is so tragic.

25:04.253 --> 25:07.715
Because you guys jumped through hoops
to get the magic out of her system...

25:07.882 --> 25:11.427
...but then her ticker is just not
strong enough to take a little siphoning.

25:11.594 --> 25:14.764
- Oh!
- Kai, you have to fix this.

25:16.557 --> 25:19.810
I can't merge tonight. I am not ready.

25:19.977 --> 25:22.813
You almost burned my house down.
Don't you think I know that?

25:22.980 --> 25:25.733
Luckily for you, it's
all been taken care of.

25:25.900 --> 25:27.527
Damon...

25:27.693 --> 25:29.904
- ...what the hell did you do?
- Look, I...

25:30.071 --> 25:31.781
[NECK SNAPS]

25:34.158 --> 25:37.245
Magical neck snap. Never gets old.

25:39.497 --> 25:41.666
Isn't this the part where
you start running?

25:41.958 --> 25:44.794
I've spent my entire life running from you.

25:45.294 --> 25:47.088
I'm not running anymore.

25:55.304 --> 25:56.973
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

26:00.601 --> 26:03.104
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS INSIDE]

26:07.316 --> 26:09.277
What are you doing out here?

26:09.443 --> 26:14.115
Just thinking about how proud I am
of you and your brother.

26:16.534 --> 26:18.661
You built a good life for yourselves here.

26:20.288 --> 26:24.625
Does that mean
you'll think about what we asked?

26:26.711 --> 26:28.004
Of course.

26:28.170 --> 26:29.213
We share a history.

26:31.173 --> 26:33.009
A bloodline.

26:36.470 --> 26:38.014
We're in this together.

26:39.515 --> 26:41.017
We're family.

26:46.022 --> 26:48.649
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

26:54.030 --> 26:55.072
You're merging us?

26:55.239 --> 26:57.366
Kai has been released. He's going after Jo.

26:57.533 --> 27:00.286
- I can't let him get to her.
- Dad, stop!

27:00.453 --> 27:02.204
I'm gonna kill her.
She's not strong enough.

27:02.371 --> 27:05.124
- I'm sorry. There's no other option.
- She's not strong enough.

27:05.291 --> 27:07.543
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

27:09.837 --> 27:10.880
She said no.

27:14.216 --> 27:15.301
Tyler!

27:15.468 --> 27:16.719
Tyler, stop!

27:22.475 --> 27:24.018
He was going to kill you.

27:24.518 --> 27:27.021
I'm fine. I'm fine.

27:32.068 --> 27:33.277
Luke, where are you going?

27:35.905 --> 27:38.741
- Do you trust me?
- Where are you going?

27:40.076 --> 27:41.619
I'll be back soon.

27:43.746 --> 27:45.414
Promise.

27:52.088 --> 27:53.964
[LIV SIGHS]

28:02.390 --> 28:04.100
Look at those pretty planets.

28:04.767 --> 28:07.478
All twinkly and bright.

28:07.645 --> 28:12.441
Oh, Josette, you would not believe
how sick I am of eclipses.

28:12.608 --> 28:14.777
Let's just get this over with.

28:16.070 --> 28:19.365
If you think I didn't spend
the last 18 years in solitary...

28:19.532 --> 28:24.537
...thinking about how you screwed me
over last time, you're wrong.

28:25.329 --> 28:27.498
So if this is just another setup...

28:27.665 --> 28:30.251
...I'll rip something out more important
than a spleen.

28:31.460 --> 28:33.421
Like a tongue...

28:33.921 --> 28:35.464
...or a heart.

28:36.590 --> 28:37.633
So...

28:37.800 --> 28:39.135
...any closing remarks?

28:39.301 --> 28:41.178
You're a parasite.

28:41.345 --> 28:43.013
You killed the people I loved.

28:43.180 --> 28:45.141
You shoved a hunting knife in my gut.

28:45.599 --> 28:47.977
You destroyed my life.

28:48.811 --> 28:50.479
Now I'm gonna destroy yours.

28:52.273 --> 28:53.774
I guess we'll see.

28:54.984 --> 28:56.277
Won't we?

28:59.780 --> 29:01.365
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

29:06.036 --> 29:07.913
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

29:24.180 --> 29:25.431
What did you just do?

29:25.598 --> 29:29.018
I just gave my big sister
a little magic knock on the head.

29:29.185 --> 29:33.189
But don't worry, she'll be fine.
Because you're gonna merge with me.

29:38.527 --> 29:40.029
[LAUGHING]

29:46.035 --> 29:47.495
Whoa.

29:49.246 --> 29:50.831
You wanna merge with me?

29:51.707 --> 29:53.959
I hate to break it to
you, little brother...

29:54.126 --> 29:55.878
...but we're not twins.

29:56.045 --> 29:58.714
- That's not how this is supposed to work.
- That's true.

29:58.881 --> 30:02.009
But we share the same parents,
the same bloodline...

30:02.176 --> 30:05.221
...and thanks to your timeout
in the magic penalty box...

30:05.387 --> 30:06.847
...we're the same age.

30:07.014 --> 30:08.682
So it's definitely a Hail Mary...

30:08.849 --> 30:11.393
...and maybe it won't work.

30:11.560 --> 30:14.522
But I'd do anything to
save my sister's life.

30:15.356 --> 30:19.443
So we're gonna give it the old college try.

30:20.069 --> 30:21.779
Thanks...

30:22.279 --> 30:23.364
...but I'm gonna pass.

30:23.531 --> 30:25.950
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

30:28.452 --> 30:29.578
What's wrong?

30:29.745 --> 30:33.916
Are you afraid to play chicken with
someone who might actually beat you?

30:36.085 --> 30:37.461
Fine.

30:39.255 --> 30:40.673
It's your funeral.

30:46.303 --> 30:47.471
Stay with me, sheriff.

30:48.472 --> 30:51.767
- Just breathe.
- Elena, hey. What happened?

30:51.934 --> 30:54.228
It's her heart. I'm losing her, Damon.

30:54.395 --> 30:58.816
- No offense, I think we need a real doctor.
- So find one. Now!

30:58.983 --> 31:00.985
[BOTH SPEAKING IN LATIN]

31:22.798 --> 31:24.258
Luke! No!

31:31.140 --> 31:33.267
Luke! Don't!

31:46.614 --> 31:48.490
No!

31:51.327 --> 31:52.870
Luke.

31:53.329 --> 31:54.496
Come on.

31:54.788 --> 31:55.998
Luke.

31:56.165 --> 31:58.459
Luke. Wake up.

31:59.126 --> 32:02.713
- How long has she been down?
- Down, what's that mean? Dead?

32:03.088 --> 32:06.383
I don't know. Maybe it was a minute.
It feels like an hour.

32:07.176 --> 32:08.385
Clear.

32:25.361 --> 32:26.403
Caroline?

32:36.830 --> 32:39.166
Honey, I'm leaving.

32:41.752 --> 32:43.504
Do you wanna say goodbye?

32:44.713 --> 32:46.215
[BEEPING RAPIDLY]

32:52.388 --> 32:57.393
I compelled you to save her. Unless you want
me to gouge your eyes out, keep working.

32:57.559 --> 33:00.562
- Here.
- I've done all that I can do. She's gone.

33:00.729 --> 33:01.897
I'm sorry.

33:02.064 --> 33:04.233
DAMON: Get out of here.
Forget you're a total failure.

33:09.071 --> 33:10.531
No. No.

33:10.698 --> 33:13.534
No, I will not let this happen.

33:14.243 --> 33:16.704
Wake up.

33:17.204 --> 33:19.581
- Hey, she's gone.
- Come on.

33:21.709 --> 33:23.752
No, no, no.

33:23.919 --> 33:26.588
Mom. Mom. Mom!

33:26.755 --> 33:29.341
Mommy! No! Mom.

33:29.717 --> 33:31.593
No!

33:32.511 --> 33:34.179
Don't leave me.

33:34.346 --> 33:36.265
Please.

33:36.432 --> 33:38.350
Please.

33:38.851 --> 33:40.436
Please don't leave me, Mom.

33:45.399 --> 33:46.442
Caroline?

33:47.526 --> 33:49.862
Didn't you hear me, sweetheart?

33:51.363 --> 33:53.282
It's time for me to go.

34:02.958 --> 34:05.294
You don't wanna say goodbye
to your mom?

34:10.174 --> 34:11.300
[GASPS]

34:11.467 --> 34:12.551
Mom?

34:12.717 --> 34:15.219
[MONITOR BEEPING NORMALLY]

34:17.347 --> 34:19.266
It's okay, baby. I'm right here.

34:19.433 --> 34:22.811
- Mom.
- Oh, it's okay. I'm right here.

34:23.478 --> 34:25.022
It's okay.

34:25.355 --> 34:26.899
I'm right here.

34:27.065 --> 34:28.692
[SOBBING]

34:29.650 --> 34:31.820
It's okay. It's okay.

34:39.786 --> 34:41.205
Where are you going?

34:41.371 --> 34:45.292
I need some air or some water
or something because...

34:47.168 --> 34:51.005
She almost died in my arms, Damon.
Caroline's mom almost died in my arms.

35:05.854 --> 35:08.232
I thought you wanted to start over.

35:08.398 --> 35:11.860
Because, FYI,
this is exactly where we left off.

35:12.653 --> 35:14.905
I don't care.

35:15.405 --> 35:19.493
Life's too short, immortal or not.
I don't wanna waste another minute.

35:44.935 --> 35:46.228
[SIGHS]

35:49.898 --> 35:51.567
Hello, stranger.

35:52.151 --> 35:53.193
H i.

35:54.111 --> 35:55.320
Are you okay?

35:57.990 --> 36:01.368
I've just been sitting here
trying to figure out what to say.

36:03.036 --> 36:07.207
I guess I should lead with
that I'm sorry for almost killing you.

36:07.374 --> 36:09.334
Oh. Sweetheart, please.

36:10.085 --> 36:13.255
You know me,
I'm the world's unluckiest gambler.

36:13.422 --> 36:16.758
I'm just sorry that I
wasn't here, I couldn't...

36:16.925 --> 36:21.763
No, no, no. This wasn't your fault.
I need you to stop beating yourself up.

36:25.267 --> 36:26.935
Can you do that for me?

36:27.102 --> 36:30.439
- Okay.
- Can you say it like you mean it?

36:32.441 --> 36:33.609
I will.

36:36.028 --> 36:39.489
Mom, you put the house in my name.

36:43.327 --> 36:45.454
Couple weeks ago.

36:47.247 --> 36:51.251
- Just in case anything...
- Yeah, well, I don't...

36:54.463 --> 36:56.506
I'm not ready for that yet.

36:56.673 --> 36:58.342
I'm sorry.

36:59.092 --> 37:03.847
And I promise you,
I will stick around as long as I can.

37:04.014 --> 37:05.140
Okay?

37:06.725 --> 37:09.686
- Okay.
- Come here.

37:23.825 --> 37:25.911
- Hey.
- Hey.

37:26.078 --> 37:29.331
- Where'd you get that?
- I guess someone fixed the coffee machine.

37:29.498 --> 37:34.127
That smells amazing. I would give you
a million dollars for a decaf latte.

37:34.544 --> 37:35.712
What do you say?

37:35.879 --> 37:38.257
Would you mind getting one
for your poor, sick mom?

37:38.423 --> 37:39.841
- I can do that.
- Okay.

37:40.008 --> 37:41.343
I'll be right back.

37:46.932 --> 37:48.433
So...

37:48.600 --> 37:51.311
...looks like we can cross miracle cure
off the list.

37:52.229 --> 37:55.774
- There must be some other option.
- I need you to promise me something.

37:55.941 --> 37:57.526
Okay.

37:57.859 --> 38:01.780
When I'm gone,
Caroline is gonna need you...

38:02.322 --> 38:04.616
...even if she doesn't know it.

38:06.034 --> 38:09.204
She's gonna need someone to help her
move on with her life...

38:09.371 --> 38:12.958
...someone to just make her smile.

38:15.544 --> 38:18.297
Promise me that you will do that, Stefan.

38:26.096 --> 38:27.889
I promise.

38:36.606 --> 38:37.733
Luke.

38:38.900 --> 38:40.652
Luke, wake up.

38:42.612 --> 38:44.156
Luke.

38:48.994 --> 38:53.707
Good. You're alive. That's gonna save me
a huge blowout with Ric when he gets back.

38:54.458 --> 38:56.918
But I'm definitely coming
into something late.

38:57.085 --> 38:59.463
Luke showed up and he merged with Kai.

38:59.629 --> 39:00.672
DAMON:
Huh.

39:00.839 --> 39:04.926
So I guess adding the words "twin merge"
to my vocabulary was pointless...

39:05.093 --> 39:06.803
...because they ain't twins.

39:06.970 --> 39:09.723
He's not supposed to be here.

39:10.182 --> 39:12.893
The only reason he's here
is because you let Kai out.

39:16.521 --> 39:17.731
Luke.

39:18.106 --> 39:20.442
Luke, wake up. Wake up, Luke.

39:21.193 --> 39:23.236
Well, uh...

39:23.695 --> 39:27.115
- I'm gonna give him some of my blood.
- It wouldn't help.

39:27.991 --> 39:29.326
It's up to them now.

39:31.203 --> 39:33.455
Whoever wakes up is the winner.

39:33.622 --> 39:35.290
And whoever doesn't...

39:37.501 --> 39:39.086
[GASPS]

39:40.545 --> 39:43.215
Can you hear me? Can you hear me?

39:43.382 --> 39:45.008
[LINE RINGING]

39:45.175 --> 39:46.760
Why the hell won't Luke call me back?

39:46.927 --> 39:48.637
- Do you want me to go look for him?
- Yes.

39:48.970 --> 39:51.014
No. I don't know.

39:51.181 --> 39:52.808
[GASPS]

39:53.517 --> 39:55.394
- Dad.
- Agh.

39:57.646 --> 39:59.022
What has your brother done?

40:00.440 --> 40:02.025
JO:
Luke.

40:03.151 --> 40:04.403
Wake up.

40:04.986 --> 40:06.863
Come on, Luke. Oh!

40:07.948 --> 40:09.574
[JO GASPS]

40:10.659 --> 40:11.827
Oh, my God.

40:12.869 --> 40:15.622
- We have to leave now.
- She's not going anywhere with you.

40:17.416 --> 40:18.458
Luke is gone.

40:19.960 --> 40:22.504
- What?
- I feel it.

40:22.671 --> 40:26.508
He merged with Kai. Kai won. Luke is gone.

40:27.592 --> 40:28.677
I don't believe you.

40:28.844 --> 40:32.055
- We have to run, Olivia.
- I'm not going anywhere with you!

40:32.431 --> 40:35.517
- You think he's gonna keep you safe?
- She's staying with me.

40:41.898 --> 40:43.942
Change your mind...

40:44.234 --> 40:45.569
...you know where to find us.

40:48.864 --> 40:50.365
TYLER:
Hey.

40:51.116 --> 40:52.701
It's okay.

40:53.285 --> 40:54.828
It's okay.

40:56.079 --> 40:58.039
JO:
Oh, my God.

40:58.790 --> 40:59.916
Luke.

41:00.083 --> 41:01.835
[SOBBING]

41:04.754 --> 41:06.339
He's gone.

41:07.757 --> 41:10.260
He saved me, and he's gone.

41:12.888 --> 41:14.306
KAI:
You win some, you lose some.

41:16.266 --> 41:18.018
Except for me.

41:18.768 --> 41:19.978
I always win.

42:01.603 --> 42:03.605
[English - US - SDH]
